org.letras.ps.region
Class DigitalInkProcessor

java.lang.Object
  org.letras.ps.region.DigitalInkProcessor

public class DigitalInkProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

The DigitalInkProcessor is responsible for ordering and generating RegionEvents. Special attention is paid to generating (continuous) trace events when region borders are crossed. The dispatch of events is delegated to the DigitalInkDispatcher.

Author:
Jannik Jochem

Method Detail

processSample

public void processSample(java.util.List<IRegion> intersectedRegions,
                          PenSample sample)
Takes a sample and a post-ordered list of regions that contain the sample and dispatches the region-normalized sample to all those regions. Also, determines whether a region boundary was crossed between this sample and the last sample. If so, processTraceCrossingRegionBorder(List, List) is called in order to generate and dispatch the necessary trace events.

Parameters:
intersectedRegions - the post-ordered list of regions that contain the sample
sample - the sample to process

processTraceCrossingRegionBorder

protected void processTraceCrossingRegionBorder(java.util.List<IRegion> previouslyIntersectedRegions,
                                                java.util.List<IRegion> intersectedRegions)
This is called when the pen crosses a region border. The following steps are performed:
  1. All regions that contained the previous sample are sent a stroke end event. The end event is continuous iff the region also contains the current sample.
  2. All regions that contain the current sample are sent a stroke start event. The start event is continuous iff the region also contains the previous sample.

Parameters:
previouslyIntersectedRegions - a post-ordered list of the locations that contained the last sample that was processed before crossing a border.
intersectedRegions - a post-ordered list of the locatons that contain the sample that is being processed after crossing the a border.

dispatchToLeafAndHungryRegions

Calls dispatch function for the first element of intersectedRegions as well as any region element that is hungry (for more).

Parameters:
intersectedRegions - a post-ordered list of regions from the region model
dispatchFunction - a functor to call for each region
